SIMPLE: osteoclast
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: osteoclast
<hw>os"te*o*clast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Osteo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>kla^n</grk> to break.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>myeloplax</er>, a
large multinucleate cell within the bone, which functions in the
absorption and removal of bone tissue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The osteoclasts occur usually in pits or cavities which
they appear to have excavated, and are supposed to be concerned in the
absorption of the bone matrix.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for performing osteoclasis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>osteocolla</ent>⟦br⟧
